{"TopicId":171537,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"KSP Head tracking?","CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-01T18:30:30Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-01T18:30:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes KSP happen to be compatible with the DIY/Low Cost TrackIR alternatives, specifically opentrack?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-02T02:11:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot familiar with open track, but there is an Arduino mod for KSP.\u00A0 It sends data over the serial port I believe, so it can control various aspects of the game from custom control boards.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/66393\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E[Hardware, Plugin] Arduino based physical display \u002B serial port io\u002B tutorial (06-Jun)\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut since IR tracking in this case is just mouse movement emulation, I don\u0027t see why you couldn\u0027t bodge together some working system.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOf course, I find KSP jittery enough on it\u0027s own, aside from IVA\u0027s, I don\u0027t really see a use for it.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klgraham1013","CreatedById":105132,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-02T02:33:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAt one point there was TrackIR support in the settings but I\u0027m not sure it ever actually worked.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"White Owl","CreatedById":10849,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-02T03:13:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt worked for one or two updates, but not very well. Last I checked, even the far-superior headtracking mod is inop.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Radiatin","CreatedById":185233,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-05T23:54:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223308075\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171537\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519960392\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002210849\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022White Owl\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/1/2018 at 10:13 PM, White Owl said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt worked for one or two updates, but not very well. Last I checked, even the far-superior headtracking mod is inop.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhich updates? KSP works standalone with no DRM so I keep a backup of each version, it\u2019s a tiny game anyway. I\u2019ve been really wanting to get plug and play Track IR working,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Archgeek","CreatedById":116048,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-06T23:18:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223311166\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171537\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520294088\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022185233\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Radiatin\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 hours ago, Radiatin said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0it\u2019s a tiny game anyway.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*Looks upon towering collection of 1.76 to 3.3 GB KSP game folders from previous versions* \u00A0*looks back up at post* ... *Looks upon terabyte HD with 330 gigs free*\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHEH. \u00A0The future is silly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pizzaoverhead","CreatedById":26349,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-07T16:39:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223308075\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171537\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519960392\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002210849\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022White Owl\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/2/2018 at 3:13 AM, White Owl said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt worked for one or two updates, but not very well. Last I checked, even the far-superior headtracking mod is inop.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYep, \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/66352-122-kerbtrack-v14-head-tracking-using-your-webcam-trackir-oculus-rift-joystick-2017-03-12/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EKerbTrack\u003C/a\u003E\u0027s been dead in the water for about a year now. I haven\u0027t had the time to get it up and running, but it\u0027s proof that it\u0027s possible for a modder to do.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pizzaoverhead","CreatedById":26349,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-14T22:23:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for posting this question. I hadn\u0027t heard of opentrack, and it\u0027s motivated me to get things up and running again. \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/66352-141-kerbtrack-v15-head-tracking-using-your-webcam-trackir-oculus-rift-joystick-2017-03-12/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EKerbTrack\u003C/a\u003E is now up to date, and supports using opentrack via the TrackIR output setting.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-14T23:04:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223321626\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171537\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221521066187\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002226349\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022pizzaoverhead\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n39 minutes ago, pizzaoverhead said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for posting this question. I hadn\u0027t heard of opentrack, and it\u0027s motivated me to get things up and running again. \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/66352-141-kerbtrack-v15-head-tracking-using-your-webcam-trackir-oculus-rift-joystick-2017-03-12/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EKerbTrack\u003C/a\u003E is now up to date, and supports using opentrack via the TrackIR output setting.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you! I can\u0027t wait to test it later this week!\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pizzaoverhead","CreatedById":26349,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-14T23:09:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223321689\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171537\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221521068648\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166583\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022dundun92\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, dundun92 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you! I can\u0027t wait to test it later this week!\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEnjoy! Let me know how it works out for you!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}